**16\. Security and Permissions**

- All data scoped by org or tenant
- RLS required on decks, deck_slides, assets, deck_exports
- Storage object policies should only allow authorized users to access objects in their org scope
- Never trust client-provided storage paths without verification
- Export routes must verify deck access before generating file

**17\. Performance Considerations**

- Load slide thumbnails lazily if deck grows
- Keep slide preview rendering pure and memoized
- Debounce rich text writes to the backend
- Persist edits incrementally, not full deck rewrites where practical
- Use server-side export to avoid browser memory spikes for large decks

**18\. Observability**

Track:

- deck created
- slide added
- slide deleted
- deck presented
- export requested
- export succeeded
- export failed
- asset uploaded

Capture export failures with slide type context for debugging.

**19\. Non-Goals for MVP**

- Real-time collaboration
- Comments
- Arbitrary custom themes
- PowerPoint import
- Freeform drawing canvas
- Embedded live charts/data integrations
- Animation timeline editor
- Template designer UI

